{
  "stem": "24364.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were all told that we have to pack our things and we have to go back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so there was tremendous excitement, obviously.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And somehow, the last minute, we were saved, because there was a transport planned from Vienna with a Mr.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Stouffer ?], who somehow had agreed to add our 320 people to his transport.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I-- really, I mean, I was too young at that time to understand how the whole thing worked.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But we were told the next day or maybe even the same day that everything is OK, don't worry, because there was tremendous excitement when they told us that we had to pack.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were waiting for that boat to arrive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at the same time, there was another coincident-- coincidence.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were Germans-- ethnic Germans who lived in Bessarabia were slated to come back to the Reich.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they needed transportation for them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And since the steamers who would take the people from Bessarabia to Germany went, you know, on the Danube and they would have had to go back empty, they decided that it was a good idea to take the Jews and let them pay for that trip, which normally would have cost them and now they could pay for the whole trip themselves, I mean with our money.",
      "word_count": 68
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that's what happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And on September 3rd, I believe, 3rd or 6th, two steamers arrived in Bratislava, the and the The [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was carrying people from Vienna.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the was carrying 500 people from Gdansk, Danzig.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were assigned to the And on September 3rd, we finally left Bratislava and got on the The Danzig people there were not very happy to see us, because the ship was terribly crowded.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
